media:group.media:description:
Religious mass gatherings will remain prohibited in the Philippines despite the easing of community quarantine restrictions across the country, MalacaÃ±ang said Tuesday. In a later clarification to reporters, Presidential Spokesman Harry Roque said religious gatherings under general community quarantine (GCQ) shall be limited to 10 people. The IATF will decide on maximum number of attendees in areas under modified general community quarantine (MGCQ) areas, he said.
